<p>Marking up abbreviations can give useful information to browsers, translation systems and search-engines.</p>


<h1> Short Quotation Marks</h1>
<p>The <q>French-Art Galaria is a beauty to behold</p>

<h1>Making abbreviations</h1>
<p>The <abbr title="World Health Oraganisation">WHO</abbr> makes policies that countries must adhere to when it comes to 
health GDP allocation.</p>

<h1>Address</h1>
<address>
Written by John Doe.<br>
Visit us at:<br>
Example.com<br>
Box 564, Disneyland<br>
USA
</address>

<h1>Cite</h1>
<p><cite>The Scream</cite> by Edward Munch in 1893.</p>

<h1>Bidirectional Override</h1>
<p><bdo dir="rtl">This text has been overriden of its direction</p>



